exports[`buildImagePrompt matches snapshot for representative RV prompt 1`] = `"Scene: photorealistic RV resort with serviced RV sites, realistic pads and utilities, and natural outdoor surroundings. Global look (fixed for this batch): Framing 4:3 landscape aspect ratio. Camera: approximately 50mm full-frame equivalent at eye level—natural perspective, avoid ultra-wide distortion. Time and light: midday neutral daylight, clear readable shadows, balanced color temperature, no artificial sunset glow unless the setting text explicitly requires it. Negatives: no people, no logos, no brand marks, no signage with readable trademarks, no overlaid text, captions, or watermarks. Composition: one clear primary subject (the glamping unit or RV site) centered in the frame at a consistent apparent scale to the ground plane; medium shot showing the full structure and immediate pad or yard; keep horizon height consistent across batch variations where applicable. Subject: Deluxe back-in. Subject constraint: this is a deluxe RV back-in site. Show a high-quality oversized level pad, clean and modern utility pedestal hookups, clear maneuvering space, premium landscaping, and a polished resort-grade appearance. Visual quality tier: Luxury — high-end outdoor hospitality infrastructure, generous level pads, lush landscaping, premium utility hardware—obvious upscale resort. Price and quality tier enforcement (RV site): "Luxury" is a primary creative constraint. Pad surface and edges, pedestal hardware, hose bibs, landscaping density, edging, and overall polish must unmistakably match that tier. Repeat: the image should be instantly readable as "Luxury" for this product visualization, not a generic compromise. Amenities: include only these, and show each clearly in the frame where realistic for the composition (e.g. visible deck, fire pit, hot tub, fencing if listed): Concrete pad. Do not show any amenities not in this list (e.g. no fire pit unless listed, no deck unless listed, no hot tub unless listed). Infrastructure: use paved internal roads and paved access surfaces that look realistic for a finished hospitality property. Default assumption: paved circulation unless Additional details (or an explicit road-surface override) clearly call for gravel or unpaved dirt. Batch: this image is 1 of 2 for one single property. Match the same terrain, vegetation, season, weather, time of day, camera height, and background horizon as the other generated images. Batch continuity: keep the exact same landscape and environmental context used for the other images in this batch: coastal pines; late afternoon. Style: genuine photograph, natural color grading, realistic exposure, no HDR or oversaturation. As if shot on a real camera—subtle shadows, authentic tones, documentary feel. Brand look: Warm but natural color grade, gentle lift in greens and earth tones, restrained contrast, premium editorial outdoor hospitality feel—avoid neon saturation or heavy HDR."`;

exports[`buildImagePrompt matches snapshot for representative glamping prompt 1`] = `"Scene: photorealistic glamping resort with distinctive lodging units in a soft natural outdoor hospitality setting. Global look (fixed for this batch): Framing 4:3 landscape aspect ratio. Camera: approximately 50mm full-frame equivalent at eye level—natural perspective, avoid ultra-wide distortion. Time and light: midday neutral daylight, clear readable shadows, balanced color temperature, no artificial sunset glow unless the setting text explicitly requires it. Negatives: no people, no logos, no brand marks, no signage with readable trademarks, no overlaid text, captions, or watermarks. Composition: one clear primary subject (the glamping unit or RV site) centered in the frame at a consistent apparent scale to the ground plane; medium shot showing the full structure and immediate pad or yard; keep horizon height consistent across batch variations where applicable. Subject: Geodesic dome, 24 foot diameter geodesic dome. Batch subject lock (image 2 of 3): the hero structure must be a Geodesic dome with silhouette and roof geometry correct for that label. An earlier batch render may show a different unit type—borrow only land, plants, sky, light, and roads from the reference; never copy the prior building’s shape when it disagrees with "Geodesic dome". Visual quality tier: Premium — high-quality, well-finished accommodations with premium touches—refined siding and trim, generous glazing quality, cohesive outdoor living details. Price and quality tier enforcement (glamping): "Premium" is a primary creative constraint. Exterior siding, glazing quality, door and trim level, deck size and railing detail, steps, and any visible interior through openings must all read at that tier—Budget must not look like a Luxury brochure; Luxury must not look like bare-bones Budget. Repeat: the image should be instantly readable as "Premium" for this product visualization, not a generic compromise. Amenities: include only these, and show each clearly in the frame where realistic for the composition (e.g. visible deck, fire pit, hot tub, fencing if listed): Hot tub, Deck. Do not show any amenities not in this list (e.g. no fire pit unless listed, no deck unless listed, no hot tub unless listed). Infrastructure: use compacted gravel internal roads and gravel access surfaces with realistic drainage and texture. Batch: this image is 2 of 3 for one single property. Match the same terrain, vegetation, season, weather, time of day, camera height, and background horizon as the other generated images. Batch continuity: keep the exact same landscape and environmental context used for the other images in this batch: shared test context. Style: genuine photograph, natural color grading, realistic exposure, no HDR or oversaturation. As if shot on a real camera—subtle shadows, authentic tones, documentary feel. Brand look: Warm but natural color grade, gentle lift in greens and earth tones, restrained contrast, premium editorial outdoor hospitality feel—avoid neon saturation or heavy HDR. Catalog reference: match the unit as closely as possible to this product page: https://catalog.example/dome. Illustrative reference for structure and finishes—product-page imagery is best-effort and may be unavailable; not an exact specification or an implied endorsement."`;
